parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the speedometer, fuel gauge, and other gauges to malfunction, leading to inaccurate readings and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Speedometer needle sticks or gives false readings
fuel gauge malfunctions
other gauges (oil pressure
temperature) redline and are inaccurate
instrument cluster failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, malfunctions, and safety risks.
symptoms: Blower motor resistor fire
HVAC blower fan failure
electrical wire harness fire
instrument panel wire harness fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift lever position indicator can cause confusion and potential safety risks while driving.
symptoms: Shift lever position indicator does not illuminate
driver is unaware of gear position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause the vehicle to stall or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel pump failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Stabilitrak and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Stabilitrak and traction control system can cause loss of control and potential safety risks while driving.
symptoms: Stabilitrak disabled
traction control off
warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: HVAC system malfunctions can cause discomfort and distraction while driving.
symptoms: HVAC blower fan failure
hot air blowing from vents
AC not working properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of power, sudden acceleration, or deceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle loses power or speed
the transmission warning light comes on
and the vehicle may not shift into gear or may get stuck in gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4WD system can cause loss of traction, loss of control, or sudden acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The "Service 4WD" light comes on
the 4WD system engages or disengages unexpectedly
the vehicle loses traction or power
the vehicle may not shift into 4WD
and the vehicle may get stuck in 4WD.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause loss of power, sudden acceleration, or deceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle may not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag system can lead to the failure of air bags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The "Service Air Bag" warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the air bag warning light is on
the air bag system is disabled
the crash sensor is faulty
the air bag sensor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crash sensor can cause the air bag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of air bags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The "Service Air Bag" warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the air bag warning light is on
the crash sensor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag sensor can cause the air bag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of air bags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The "Service Air Bag" warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the air bag warning light is on
the air bag sensor is faulty.
